</p>
<p>The etiquette of condolence messages hinges on sincerity and respect. Avoid clichés or platitudes that might minimize the depth of their loss. Instead, focus on expressing genuine sympathy and offering practical support where possible.  Remember to keep the focus on the deceased and their positive qualities, celebrating their life and legacy.  Finally, ensure your message is delivered with care and consideration, ensuring it arrives at the appropriate time and through a channel the recipient will appreciate.</p>
    

